 McDonald's All-American\n* 2 players named McDonald's All-American MVP\n\nArizona also holds several other NCAA records and various additional accomplishments:\n* Arizona has 1 NCAA championship (1997), 2 Maui Invitational Championships (2000, 2014), 29 Fiesta Bowl Classic championships (1974\u201375, 1985\u201398, 2001\u201308, 2010\u201312), 16 Pac-10/12 regular-season championships, and a league best 7 Pac-10/12 Tournament championships.\n\n===All-Time Statistical leaders===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Points\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Name</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Years</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Points</span>\n|- \n| Sean Elliott\n| 1985-89\n| 2,555\n|- \n| Bob Elliott\n| 1973-77\n| 2,131\n|- \n| Jason Gardner\n| 1999-2003\n| 1,984\n|- \n| Salim Stoudamire\n| 2001-05\n| 1,960\n|- \n| Khalid Reeves\n| 1990-94\n| 1,925\n|- \n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Freshman Points\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Name</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Years</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Points</span>\n|- \n| Deandre Ayton\n| 2018\n| 704\n|- \n| Jerryd Bayless\n| 2008\n| 592\n|- \n| Coniel Norman\n| 1973\n| 576\n|- \n| Lauri Markkanen\n| 2017\n| 576\n|- \n| Gilbert Arenas\n| 2000\n| 523\n|- \n| Stanley Johnson\n| 2015\n| 523\n|- \n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Rebounds\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Name</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Years</span>\n! style=\"background:#00407a;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Rebounds</span>\n|- \n| Al Fleming\n| 1973-76\n| 1,190\n|- \n| Bob Elliott\n| 1974-77\n| 1,083\n|- \n| Channing Frye\n| 2001-05\n| 975\n|- \n| Kaleb Tarczewski\n| 2013-16\n| 879\n|- \n| Anthony Cook\n| 1986-89\n| 861\n|- \n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Freshm