son, AP provided a preseason (PS) poll. AP did a post-tournament poll in 1953, 1954, 1974 and 1975. The following table summarizes Arizona history in the [[AP Poll]]:<ref>{{cite news|url=http://collegepollarchive.com/mbasketball/ap/teams/summary.cfm?teamid=48#.XeVYiehKiUk|title=Arizona AP Men's Basketball Poll Summary|access-date=|page=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Arizona Wildcats|Year|Appearances|Pct|High|Low|Average|Final Ranking}}\n|-\n|2020\n|13\n|{{pct|13|18}}\n|12\n|25\n|19\n|TBD\n|-\n|2018\n|17\n|{{pct|17|19}}\n|2\n|23\n|13\n|12\n|-\n|2017\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|4\n|20\n|11\n|4\n|-\n|2016\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|7\n|23\n|14\n|17\n|-\n|2015\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|2\n|10\n|5\n|5\n|-\n|2014\n|20\n|{{pct|20|20}}\n|1\n|6\n|3\n|4\n|-\n|2013\n|20\n|{{pct|20|20}}\n|3\n|21\n|10\n|21\n|-\n|2012\n|3\n|{{pct|3|19}}\n|15\n|23\n|18\n|NR\n|-\n|2011\n|7\n|{{pct|7|19}}\n|10\n|20\n|16\n|17\n|-\n|2008\n|7\n|{{pct|7|20}}\n|17\n|22\n|19\n|NR\n|-\n|2007\n|15\n|{{pct|15|19}}\n|7\n|24\n|14\n|NR\n|-\n|2006\n|8\n|{{pct|8|19}}\n|9\n|24\n|17\n|24\n|-\n|2005\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|8\n|21\n|13\n|9\n|-\n|2004\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|3\n|22\n|11\n|22\n|-\n|2003\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|1\n|4\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|2002\n|17\n|{{pct|17|18}}\n|4\n|20\n|12\n|7\n|-\n|2001\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|1\n|21\n|9\n|5\n|-\n|2000\n|19\n|{{pct|19|19}}\n|2\n|10\n|5\n|4\n|-\n|1999\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|6\n|18\n|10\n|12\n|-\n|1998\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|1\n|8\n|4\n|4\n|-\n|1997\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|6\n|19\n|12\n|15\n|-\n|1996\n|17\n|{{pct|17|18}}\n|3\n|19\n|11\n|11\n|-\n|1995\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|5\n|15\n|10\n|15\n|-\n|1994\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|6\n|19\n|12\n|9\n|-\n|1993\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|3\n|22\n|10\n|5\n|-\n|1992\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|2\n|11\n|6\n|10\n|-\n|1991\n|17\n|{{pct|17|17}}\n|2\n|9\n|5\n|8\n|-\n|1990\n|17\n|{{pct|17|17}}\n|2\n|24\n|18\n|14\n|-\n|1989\n|18\n|{{pct|18|18}}\n|1\n|12\n|6\n|1\n|-\n|1988\n|17\n|{{pct|17|17}}\n|1\n|17\n|3\n|2\n|-\n|1987\n|2\n|{{pct|2|19}}\n|19\n|20\n|20\n|NR\n|-\n|1985\n|1\n|{{pct|1|18}}\n|19\n|19\n|19\n|NR\n|-\n|1977\n|15\n|{{pct|15|17}}\n|8\n|20\n|14\n|NR\n|-\n|1976\n|5\n|{{pct|5|17}}\n|10\n|18\n|13\n|15\n|-\n|1975\n|15\n|{{pct|15|19}}\n|10\n|19\n|15\n|NR\n|-\n|1974\n|8\n|{{pct|8|18}}\n|12\n|20\n|15\n|NR\n|-\n|1951\n|8\n|{{pct|8|12}}\n|11\n|16\n|14\n|12\n|-\n|1950\n|5\n|{{pct|5|10}}\n|15\n|19\n|17\n|15\n|-\n|}\n\n===Arizona vs. the AP Top 25===\nThe Wildcats all-time record versus ranked teams is 148\u2013185 ({{Winning percentage|148|185}}).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/arizona.sidearmsports.com/documents/2018/10/24/Arizona_Basketball_Online_Media_Guide.pdf|title=Arizona Basketball Online Media Guide 2018-2019|access-date=2018-11-22|page=64}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Arizona Wildcats|Rank|Record|Last Met|Opponent|Result|Score}}\n|-\n|No. 1\n|4\u20134\n|3/26/05\n|[[Illinois Fighting Illini men's basketball|Illinois]]\n|L\n|89\u201390 (ot)\n|-\n|No. 2\n|4\u201311\n|12/29/07\n|[[Memphis Tigers men's basketball|Memphis]]\n|L\n|63\u201376\n|-\n|No. 3\n|10\u20136\n|11/20/18\n|[[Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball|Gonzaga]]\n|L\n|74\u201391\n|-\n|No. 4\n|7\u201316\n|12/14/08\n|Gonzaga\n|W\n|69\u201364\n|-\n|No. 5\n|8\u201312\n|3/11/17\n|[[Oregon Ducks men's basketball|Oregon]]\n|W\n|83\u201380\n|-\n|No. 6\n|8\u201314\n|12/14/19\n|Gonzaga\n|L\n|80\u201384\n|-\n|No. 7\n|7\u20137\n|12/5/17\n|[[Texas A&M Aggies men's basketball|Texas A&M]]\n|W\n|67\u201364\n|-\n|No. 8\n|11\u201313\n|11/21/18\n|[[Auburn Tigers men's basketball|Auburn]]\n| L\n| 57\u201373\n|-\n|No. 9\n|10\u20137\n|1/9/20\n|Oregon\n|L\n|73\u201374 (ot)\n|-\n|No. 10\n|4\u20139\n|1/27/05\n|[[Washington Huskies men's basketball|Washington]]\n|W\n|91\u201382\n|-\n|No. 11\n|2\u20134\n|2/14/09\n|[[UCLA Bruins men's basketball|UCLA]]\n|W\n|84\u201372\n|-\n|No. 12\n|2\u20136\n|11/12/16\n|[[Michigan State Spartans men's basketball|Michigan State]]\n|W\n|65\u201363\n|-\n|