ayer Award|NBA Finals MVP]], United States \u2013 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Gold medal, NBA All-Rookie Team, NBA All-star, 2x NBA All-Defensive Team, NBA Dunk Contest participant (2006) \n|-\n| [[Solomon Hill (basketball)|Solomon Hill]]\n| Miami Heat\n| 2009\u201313\n|\n|-\n| [[Aaron Gordon]]\n| [[Orlando Magic]]\n| 2013\u201314\n| 3x NBA Dunk Contest participant (2016, 2017 & 2020) \n|-\n| [[Rondae Hollis-Jefferson]]\n| [[Toronto Raptors]]\n| 2013\u201315\n|\n|-\n| [[Stanley Johnson (basketball)|Stanley Johnson]]\n| Toronto Raptors\n| 2014\u201315\n|\n|-\n| [[T. J. McConnell]]\n| [[Indiana Pacers]]\n| 2013\u201315\n|\n|-\n| [[Kadeem Allen]]\n| [[New York Knicks]]\n| 2014\u201317\n| Currently on a two-way contract playing with the [[Westchester Knicks]]\n|-\n| [[Lauri Markkanen]]\n| [[Chicago Bulls]]\n| 2016\u201317\n| [[NBA All-Rookie Team|NBA All-Rookie 1st Team]] (2018)\n|-\n| [[Kobi Simmons]]\n| [[Charlotte Hornets]]\n| 2016\u221217\n| Currently on a two-way contract playing with the [[Greensboro Swarm]]\n|-\n| [[Deandre Ayton]]\n| [[Phoenix Suns]]\n| 2017\u201318\n|First Arizona Wildcat to be selected 1st overall, [[NBA All-Rookie Team|NBA All-Rookie 1st Team]] (2019)\n|-\n| [[Allonzo Trier]]\n| [[New York Knicks]]\n| 2015\u201318\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n====NBA G League players====\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Arizona Wildcats|Name|NBA team|Seasons as Wildcat|Post-Wildcat accomplishment}}\n|-\n| Brandon Randolph\n| [[Wisconsin Herd]]\n| 2017\u201319\n| \n|-\n|}\nSource: Arizona 2018-19 Media Guide<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.arizonawildcats.com/documents/2017/10/31/2017_18_Arizona_Basketball_Media_Guide_Online_.pdf|title=2017-18 Media Guide |date=October 31, 2017|accessdate=February 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''''Current non-NBA professional players'''''\n* [[Rawle Alkins]] \u2212 [[FC Porto (basketball)|FC Porto]] (Portugal)\n* [[Jerryd Bayless]] \u2212 [[Sichuan Blue Whales]] (China)\n* Parker Jackson\u2212Cartwright \u2212 [[Cheshire Phoenix]] (England)\n* [[Daniel Dillon (basketball)|Daniel Dillon]] \u2013 [[Adelaide 36ers]] (Australia) & [[SKS Starogard Gda\u0144ski]] (Poland)\n* [[Kyle Fogg]] \u2013 [[Beijing Royal Fighters]] (China)\n* [[Grant Jerrett]] \u2013 [[Ratiopharm Ulm]] (Germany)\n* [[Nick Johnson (basketball)|Nick Johnson]] \u2013 [[T\u00fcrk Telekom B.K.]] (Turkey)\n* [[Mark Lyons]] \u2013 [[Hapoel Tel Aviv B.C.]] (Israeli)\n* [[Kyrylo Natyazhko]] \u2013 [[BC Dnipro]] (Ukraine)\n* [[Keanu Pinder]] \u2013 [[Legia Warszawa (basketball)|Legia Warszawa]] (Poland)\n* [[Du\u0161an Risti\u0107]] \u2013 [[KK Crvena zvezda]] (Serbia) on loan with [[BC Astana]] (Kazakhstan)\n* [[Kaleb Tarczewski]] \u2013 [[Pallacanestro Olimpia Milano|AX Armani Exchange Olimpia Milan]] (Italy)\n* [[Mark Tollefsen]] \u2013 [[Maccabi Ashdod B.C.]] (Israel)\n* [[Derrick Williams (basketball)|Derrick Williams]] \u2013 [[Fenerbah\u00e7e Basketball|Fenerbah\u00e7e]] (Turkey)\n* [[Gabe York]] \u2013 [[SIG Basket]] (France)\n* [[Brandon Ashley]] \u2013 [[New Zealand Breakers]] (New Zealand)\n\n====NBA Draft history====\n{{Main|List of Arizona Wildcats in the NBA Draft}}\n\n12 different NBA championships have been won by 10 Wildcats players. Since the NBA draft was shortened to two rounds in 1989, 41 Arizona players have been selected. Former Wildcats have had successful NBA careers, totaling over $1.4 billion in total contracts through the 2019\u20132020 NBA season<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/arizona.sidearmsports.com/documents/2016/10/26/Final_2016_17_Media_Guide_for_Online.pdf|title=Arizona Media Guide|last=|first=|date=|website=arizonawildcats.com |publisher=|access-date=2017-01-27}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Arizona Wildcats|Name|Round|Overall Pick|Year|Team}}\n|-\n| [[Morris Udall]]\n| ...\n| ...\n| 1948\n| [[Denver Nuggets (original)|Denver Nuggets]] ([[National Basketball League (United States)|NBL]])\n|-\n| Lincoln Richmond\n| ...\n| 